setup sublime: 

install http://tipsonubuntu.com/2017/05/30/install-sublime-text-3-ubuntu-16-04-official-way/

install sublime in ubuntu 22.04 https://www.how2shout.com/linux/2-ways-to-install-sublime-text-3-on-ubuntu-22-04-20-04/

1. follow the tutorial here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zVLJfrIwEP8 
then install package control 
    - color scheme "dayle rees color scheme "
install https://packagecontrol.io/packages/Colorsublime 

In the preferences of sublime, select color scheme accordingly  
initially try different color schemes: kane, nature, neon_kush, neonglow, solarsooty, warmneon, bashling, agoladark, adventure_time, darkside, yuba, glowfish, easyball, ILMHacker 
   - theme 
try different themes according to https://dev.to/kazup/10-best-sublime-text-themes-in-2018-53j5 
and https://speckyboy.com/free-themes-sublime-text/ 
now choose "Adaptive.sublime-theme" and "easyball" colorscheme 

install tools:
- brackethighlighter 
- sidebarenhancement 
- sublimecodeintel
optional emmet 
- sublimelinter ? 
- origami
- cobalt2  (only a theme, not installed)

Font: firacode
https://github.com/tonsky/FiraCode/wiki/Sublimetext-Instructions
install each font by double clicking 
https://github.com/tonsky/FiraCode/wiki/Linux-instructions#installing-with-a-package-manager 

install CMakeEditor to analyze CMakeLists file 

in the end my user settings:
{
"color_scheme": "Packages/Colorsublime - Themes/cache/Colorsublime-Themes-master/themes/Easyballs.tmTheme",
"font_size": 10,
"ignored_packages":
[
"Vintage"
],
"save_on_focus_lost": true,
"sidebar_front_big": true,
"theme": "Adaptive.sublime-theme",
"font_face": "Fira Code Medium",
"font_options":
[
"subpixel_antialias"
]
}
